CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 4, 1959, pg. A3, reads: "Platform Guests - Seated on the platform ground-breaking ceremonies, are outstanding civic, county and city officials, including Mrs. R. L. Vann and Mrs. W. W. Stanton, widows of former Loendi presidents. Also in picture are Mrs. Mary MacEnheimer, Councilman Paul F. Jones, and W. A. Harris, Sr., chairman of the event. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Crowd gathered around small pavilion with bunting, including Paul F. Jones and William "Woogie" Harris facing away and standing near flag on right, and Jessie Vann seated inside, for groundbreaking ceremony of Loendi Club on Ledlie Street
